Articles.Content:
Welcome to the archives. We document notable missions of the Jedi Space Program. Scientific reports, anecdotes and general writings will also be documented here.

Key

The basic summary next to the link will be in one of the following colors, denoting it's current status:

Blue--Ongoing. This document is not yet completed.

Green--Finished. This document has been completed.

Yellow--Postponed. This document has been delayed for some reason, but still has a chance of being completed. Do not expect updates for a while.

Red--This document has been cancelled, with little to no chance of being completed. Listed here simply for the curious.

Contents

Dramatis personÃƒÂ¦--An ongoing log of every kerbal ever to appear in our tales!

Clean Slate, Part One--The beginning of the Clean Slate story arc! The mysterious Erasers come, and the words of the monolith near the KSC are revealed...

The Diary of Bill Kerman--AKA Clean Slate, Part Two! Bill is searching the Mun for the Armstrong Memorial, and finds many other strange things on his travels. This is his firsthand account of his adventures and misadventures as the most alone kerbal in the solar system. Cancelled due to 0.23.

Sidgun and Nellas--A short tale of how Sidgun and Nellas became interested in space travel. It was the most important moment in their lives...

Voyage of the OdinBill and Roning go to Dres, with... interesting results...

The Godspeed program--The Jedi Space Program has a new plan: Land on an asteroid! Can they do it?

The Legend Of Santa Jeb--Jeb is going to the Mun for Christmas! Based on the Kadvent Kalendar challenge.

More coming soon!

Edited December 6, 2014 by The Jedi Master
